  "title": "Fix undesired history push when history changed with search params",
  "body": "<!--\n  Thanks for submitting a pull request!\n  Please provide enough information so that others can review your pull request.\n-->\n\n**Summary**\n\nIn some SPAs instantsearch.js router will inappropriately write an undesirable new history state. The source from what I found is that the `createURL` method does not take into account existing search params which ultimately leads the `shouldWrite` method not return the correct boolean value.\n\nBy taking into account existing search params in `createURL` we fix these undesireable `window.history.pushState` calls coming from the library.\n\nA demo of the bug and the fix can be viewed here:\nhttps://www.loom.com/share/45df116aab104f7086c5c45932cba0dd\n\n<!--\n  Explain the **motivation** for making this change.\n  What existing problem does the pull request solve?\n  Are there any linked issues?\n-->\n\n**Result**\n\nThe Loom linked above demos the corrected behavior from this fix. Additionally unit tests have been updated to reflect this corrected behavior as well.\n\n<!--\n  Demonstrate the code is solid.\n  Example: The exact commands you ran and their output,\n  screenshots / videos if the pull request changes UI.\n\n  You will be able to test out these changes on the deploy\n  preview (address will be commented by a bot):\n\n  1. the documentation site (/)\n  2. a widget playground (/stories)\n-->\n",
